english:
  title: Edict Appointing the Crown Prince
  author: Lee Jang-yong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Thus it is proclaimed. The King speaks: The foundation laid by our ancestors through generations shall expand through the grant of succession, and the enduring root of the realm shall flourish through the establishment of the rightful heir. It is fitting that we elevate the one and only worthy successor, thereby manifesting renewed splendor and blessing.

    Hear now, O Crown Prince: You are endowed with gentleness and refined learning, graced with harmony and magnanimous spirit. Your filial devotion flows naturally from your heart, and your daily inquiries show no faltering. Your studies advance without need of ardent instruction, progressing month by month. Reverent and respectful, you have conquered selfish desire; your bearing is dignified and accords with propriety. When we journeyed to the northern territories, the capital fell silent in our absence. Responding to the people's hopes, we entrusted you with the authority of regent. When foreign emissaries arrived, you received them with excellence. All rejoiced, and we were greatly pleased.

    Though the signs of heaven's approval have appeared, the ceremonies of the Eastern Palace remain incomplete. We have selected an auspicious day, now deemed propitious, and hereby publish this grand decree. Now we dispatch our official, bearing the imperial seal and carrying full ceremonial honors, to proclaim you Crown Prince.

    Ah, there is no path to honoring your forebears greater than benevolence, and no principle for continuing the royal lineage save virtue. Distance yourself from flatterers that righteous men draw near; heed virtuous counsel that worthy reputation spreads. Thus shall you establish lasting excellence for ten thousand ages and eternally fulfill the hopes of the three kingdoms and all their people. Is this not most glorious?
  footnotes:
    - The 'three kingdoms' (三韓) refers to ancient Korea's three major regions and peoples—a poetic reference to the realm as a whole.
